OL,6,FIn a statement, Sunderland AFC said:
OL,7,F"SAFC's Board of Directors, players
OL,8,Fand staff wish Tony a swift recovery
OL,9,Fand our thoughts are with him and his
OL,10,Ffamily at this moment in time.J"We
OL,11,Fknow these sentiments are also held by
OL,12,Four supporters throughout the world,
OL,13,Fwho continue to hold an immense
OL,14,Frespect for our former Head Coach."
OL,16,FMeanwhile Middlesbrough FC said in a
OL,17,Fpost on X: "Get well soon Mogga,
OL,18,Fwishing you all the very best from
OL,19,Feveryone at MFC."
